# PaperChat MVP Project Overview

This is a Next.js MVP for PaperChat - an AI-powered PDF chat application. The project follows the specifications in [TODO.md](mdc:TODO.md).

## Core Concept
Users upload a PDF and can ask questions about it through a chat interface. The AI responds based on the PDF content.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js (pages router) + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Backend**: Node.js/Express (API routes)
- **PDF Processing**: pdf-parse library
- **AI**: OpenAI API
- **Storage**: In-memory only (no database)
- **Deployment**: Vercel

## Key Features (MVP)
1. PDF Upload with validation (max 10MB)
2. Sample PDF demo mode
3. Basic chat interface with OpenAI integration
4. Feedback loop (thumbs up/down)
5. Split layout: PDF viewer + chat interface

## Project Structure
- `/pages` - Next.js pages and API routes
- `/components` - React components
- `/utils` - Utility functions
- `/public` - Static assets

